Flow

Deploy.s.sol deploys MemoryLending.sol with an injected ERC-8004 identity registry address.
publish-fragment.ts copies a source markdown file into fragments/, hashes the served copy, and publishes metadata plus contentURI to the lending contract.
serve-fragments.ts exposes fragments/ over local HTTP.
borrow-fragment.ts reads fragment metadata from chain, fetches contentURI, verifies the hash, then sends the borrow payment transaction.
give-feedback.ts is meant to push post-borrow feedback to ERC-8004 reputation.
evaluate.ts is fully off-chain: it loads tasks, loads local fragments, runs baseline and augmented Claude calls, then writes JSON results.
What the contract currently enforces

MemoryLending.sol now depends on IIdentityRegistry.sol.
On publishFragment, it checks ownerOf(contributorAgentId) == msg.sender.
On borrowFragment, it checks ownerOf(borrowerAgentId) == msg.sender.
It does not fetch fragment bytes itself; content stays off-chain behind the HTTP server.
Important caveat

The reputation path is architecturally present, but per the current review it is still not interoperable with the live ERC-8004 registry because the ABI in config.ts is still mismatched.
